      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:1:57:12",
      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/57/1100",
      "text": [
        " بِقَوْلِكَ وَ اَلْمُجَاهِرُ بِالْفِسْقِ وَ إِنْ كَانَ مُقْتَصِداً."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.1110 - Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) said:\n\"Three people should not be prayed behind: the one who is unknown (al-majhūl), the extremist (al-ghālī) even if he claims to hold your beliefs, and the one who openly commits sinful acts (al-mujāhir bil-fisq) even if he appears moderate.\""
        ]
      }
    },
